The git push output is provided in the tool_response tag below:
<tool_response>{{ git_push_response }}</tool_response>

From the tool_response, extract the pushed branch name. Use it as BRANCH_NAME below.

<step number="1">
  Use the `create_merge_request` tool to open a new merge request:
  create_merge_request(
      project_id={{ project_id }},
      source_branch=BRANCH_NAME,
      target_branch="{{ source_branch or default_branch }}",
      title="Draft: [FixPipeline] {{ pipeline_url }}",
      description="",
  )
  DO NOT include a "labels" parameter.
</step>

<step number="2">
  Use the `update_merge_request` tool to update the merge request description with a summary of what was changed:
  <execution_output>
    {{ execution_results }}
  </execution_output>

  Add this text at the bottom of the description:
  <text>
    Fixes [failing pipeline]({{ pipeline_url }})<br><br>[Session {{ workflow_id }}]({{ session_url }})
  </text>

  Also set assignee_id to `{{ assignee_id }}`.
</step>
